        {
          "question": "<p>Correct the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n\t<li>The motion of a swing is an example of rectilinear motion.</li>\r\n\t<li>1m = 1000 cm</li>\r\n</ol>",
          "id": 478199,
          "options_data": [],
          "solution_data": [
            {
              "id": 255926,
              "solution": "<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n\t<li>The motion of a swing is an example of periodic motion as its motion is repeated after a fixed interval of time.</li>\r\n\t<li>1m = 100 cm.&nbsp;Each metre (m) is divided into 100 equal divisions&nbsp;called centimetre (cm).</li>\r\n</ol>"
            }
          ],
